The test is still failing. The issue might be that the test scenario might be using a DEFLATED entry rather than a STORED entry. Looking back at the test data in StepDefs.java, I see that the compression method was set to 0x0800, which corresponds to DEFLATED. Let me also update the DEFLATED handling part to catch truncated entries.

In the DEFLATED portion of the `read` method, I need to also handle the case where the inflater finishes before we expect it to (indicating a truncated entry). Let me check what compression method is being used in the step definition. The value 0x0800 in the test data corresponds to DEFLATED compression.

Looking at the DEFLATED section of the read method:
